Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly butter one 9x9 inch pan. Mix together the apples, mincemeat and lemon juice. Place in prepared pan. In a medium bowl, stir together the flour, nuts, sugar and oats; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over apple mixture. Bake at 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) for 45 minutes or until apples are tender.